# Rasm Rhino Exchange Camera Blocks

Read `libs/csharp/Rasm.Rhino/AGENTS.md` and verify named Rhino members through local XML/decompile evidence.

## Category Owners

| Folder | Owns |
| --- | --- |
| `Exchange/` | File capabilities, archive/publish/import/export, sheet edits, linked resources, raster/PDF policy, and typed receipts. |
| `Camera/` | Viewport target resolution, live camera state, camera mutation, projections, frustums, named views, capture, and sequencing. |
| `Blocks/` | Block definitions, instances, live/archive linked state, placement, replacement, graph/audit, events, cleanup, preview/export, and management. |

## Rules

- Capture full Rhino capability behind one operation rail per category; do not mirror native calls as public wrappers.
- Preserve document receipts, redraw/commit behavior, resource lifetimes, and native consistency in the category boundary.
- Keep document mutation, selection, construction, UI, camera, and exchange ownership separated.
- Use current RhinoWIP API evidence. Do not rely on GH1, Rhino 8, Windows, or stale public examples.

## Validation

Use `bash scripts/check-cs.sh check`; add tests or bridge checks when runtime document, viewport, block, file, or capture behavior changes.
